2009-06-23 by mark williamson

   * Fixed bug where temporary filename was constructed without a '/' after the 
      /tmp part meaning it could only be run as root because it tried to make temp files
      in / on the filesystem. 


2008-11-17 to 2009-06-16 by "voidptrptr":

	* Fix bug on Linux machine only wich appears after truncating a temporary record file
	  when using compressed record without extra field (ex. Heritrix WARC files).
	  This bug was reported by Noah from Internet Archive. Thanks dude !

2008-11-14 to 2008-11-17 by "voidptrptr":

	* Java wrapper for warc tools (see contrib/java/install)
	* JHOVE integration for validating WARC files (see contrib/jhove/install)


2008-11-07 to 2008-11-14 by "voidptrptr":

        * Fix mahjor bug on SWIG when moving to 64 bits WARC file size support
	* WARC browser bsed proxy (see contrib/browser/readme)


2008-10-22 to 2008-11-07 by "voidptrptr":

        * Fix doc typo
	* Unlock WARC file size limit to use warc_u64_t (handle Exa bytes WARC file). 

2008-09-14 to 2008-10-22 by "voidptrptr":

	* Fix minor bugs
        * Add Ruby SWIG wrapper (plugin/ruby and app/ruby)

2008-09-12 to 2008-09-14 by "voidptrptr":

	* Add pages man for C commands ans update the security model

2008-09-10 to 2008-09-12 by "voidptrptr":

	* Full functional release of HTTrack WARC plugin, ready to use (contrib/httrack)

2008-09-08 to 2008-09-10 by "voidptrptr":

	* WARC storage backend for HTTrack (contrib/httrack)

2008-05-29 to 2008-09-08 by "voidptrptr":

	* Complete rewrite of the Python wrapper
	* Curl integration with pyCurl (contrib/curl)
	* HTTrack collections migration tool (contrib/httrack)

2008-04-06 to 2008-05-29 by "voidptrptr":

	* Full Python wrapper implementation

2008-02-15 to 2008-04-06 by "voidptrptr":

	* Second stable release. Compliant with WARC/0.17 specification

2008-02-08 to 2008-02-15 by "voidptrptr":

	* Stable release. Compliant with WARC/0.9 specification

2007-11-20 to 2008-02-08 by "voidptrptr":

	* First candidate release.
